Package: lindia
Type: Package
Title: Linear Regression Diagonostic Plots in GGPlot
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Yeuk Yu", "Lee", 
    email = "lyeukyu@gmail.com", 
    role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Samuel", "Ventura", 
    email = "sventura@stat.cmu.edu", 
    role = c("aut")))
Description: Allows easy generation of linear regression diagnostic plots 
    in GGPlot. Graph types include residual plots, QQPlot, boxcox graph, 
    scale-location plot, cook's distance plot, and residual leverage plot. 
    This package is meant for easy scheming of linear regression diagnostics. 
    See the ggplot2 website for more information regarding the functionality 
    of ggplot.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.2)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Imports:
    MASS,
    ggplot2,
    gridExtra
URL: https://github.com/yeukyul/lindia
BugReports: https://github.com/yeukyul/lindia/issues
